{"TopicId":191394,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"Varying Music on Exoplanets","CreatedByName":"Delfino42","CreatedById":202634,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-03T16:10:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Delfino42","CreatedById":202634,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-03T16:10:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI Have loved kerbal space program for a while now and I\u0027ve done many missions to the surface of other planets/moons. One thing that i have noticed with the atmospheric planets. When you land it still plays the music as if you were in space. I think it would be cool if in ksp 2 there would be different music sets for planets/moons with atmospheres or different music set when you go to other solar systems. This is purely an aesthetic thing but something that would really set forward the idea of landing on a far away foreign planet.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-03T19:49:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they really wanted to go all-in on it, they could even have different themes for different planets...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like KSP\u0027s music, but I\u0027ll admit it\u0027s not really up to a professional game studio\u0027s level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-03T20:10:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223735815\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191394\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221580746205\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022202634\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Delfino42\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Delfino42 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI Have loved kerbal space program for a while now and I\u0027ve done many missions to the surface of other planets/moons. One thing that i have noticed with the atmospheric planets. When you land it still plays the music as if you were in space. I think it would be cool if in ksp 2 there would be different music sets for planets/moons with atmospheres or different music set when you go to other solar systems. This is purely an aesthetic thing but something that would really set forward the idea of landing on a far away foreign planet.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223735903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191394\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221580759369\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DStaal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, DStaal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they really wanted to go all-in on it, they could even have different themes for different planets...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like KSP\u0027s music, but I\u0027ll admit it\u0027s not really up to a professional game studio\u0027s level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can do that with the Sound Track Editor mod (you can get a working copy for 1.8 here:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/SoundtrackEditor/releases/tag/4.3.2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/SoundtrackEditor/releases/tag/4.3.2\u003C/a\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-03T20:14:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223735912\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191394\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221580760650\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can do that with the Sound Track Editor mod (you can get a working copy for 1.8 here:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/SoundtrackEditor/releases/tag/4.3.2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/SoundtrackEditor/releases/tag/4.3.2\u003C/a\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure - but I\u0027d still have to pick out the music.\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 Getting good music for it is really the hard part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRelevant video I watched recently:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/b0gvM4q2hdI?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mattinoz","CreatedById":118580,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-05T01:39:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t they?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe bad assumption on my part but given there is a guy in dev video as music producer saying he\u0027s crafting sound tracks to various parts of the game and talks about binary system I kind of thought I was odd if he was full time just reworking boppy \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E music.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Satellitefanatic","CreatedById":202670,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-10T00:26:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe current soundtrack\u00A0for KSP is Kevin Macleod\u00A0music (which is copyright-free)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-10T00:28:14Z\u0022 title=\u002202/10/2020 12:28  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 10, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Satellitefanatic\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dirkidirk","CreatedById":200064,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-10T00:42:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223738609\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191394\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581294414\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022202670\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Satellitefanatic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Satellitefanatic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe current soundtrack\u00A0for KSP is Kevin Macleod\u00A0music (which is copyright-free)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nok, so?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nprobable answer: \u0022just wanted to point that out\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Satellitefanatic","CreatedById":202670,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-10T01:20:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis means that the implementation of MOAR MUSIC should not be that difficult.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-10T16:33:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223738620\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191394\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581297647\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022202670\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Satellitefanatic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, Satellitefanatic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis means that the implementation of MOAR MUSIC should not be that difficult.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot difficult at all:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8853562389\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/191467-173-18x-soundtrack-editor-forked/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Empiro","CreatedById":112072,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-10T21:52:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving unique music for different situations and planets would definitely go a long way to making KSP 2 better. I already have the soundtrack editor for KSP1, but I definitely don\u0027t want to have to take the time to select each track for each planet / situation separately.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would also be nice for KSP 2 to have a composer creating unique music just for the game, rather than using free music.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Satellitefanatic","CreatedById":202670,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-11T06:43:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue, and as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003Ehave\u00A0shown, it is also very easy to mod custom music into the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-11T06:44:44Z\u0022 title=\u002202/11/2020 06:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 11, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Satellitefanatic\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}